:::summary
The steam engine is one of the most consequential inventions in human history — the machine that made the Industrial Revolution possible and transformed how people lived, worked, and moved across the earth. By harnessing the expansive power of steam generated from boiling water, engineers converted heat energy into mechanical work on a scale that no animal, wind, or waterwheel could match. The story of the steam engine is a story of human ingenuity — of craftsmen, scientists, and entrepreneurs working together under God's provision to lift millions out of poverty and reshape civilization.
